me": "control-slab", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "3902d795-a30f-41a4-a732-19ce0ede87af"}, {"name": "volc-pinatubo-slab", "furtherInfo": "3", "canonicalName": "volc-pinatubo-slab", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "f83b4c1e-1b3b-44e6-a692-2800f41da685"}, {"name": "dcppC-forecast-addPinatubo", "furtherInfo": "1", "canonicalName": "dcppC-forecast-addPinatubo", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "6b98a9d0-d1da-499a-9f28-600c62b698ff"}, {"name": "volc-cluster-mill", "furtherInfo": "3", "canonicalName": "volc-cluster-mill", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "83090de9-eed0-4e46-b5d9-a8c046724788"}, {"name": "volc-cluster-21C", "furtherInfo": "3", "canonicalName": "volc-cluster-21C", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "78161292-81f8-41b5-b91f-0fd191affff1"}, {"name": "volc-long-hlS", "furtherInfo": "3", "canonicalName": "volc-long-hlS", "version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.designing.NumericalExperiment", "id": "e4b84ccf-5644-46c5-b859-31a154c19802"}], "objectives": ["Dynamics: Improve understanding of the (seasonal to interannual) mechanisms underlying the dynamical atmospheric response to large volcanic eruptions, in particular separating indirect responses from the direct radiative response; improve understanding of decadal feedback mechanisms induced in the coupled ocean-atmosphere system by large volcanic eruptions.", "Evaluation: Evaluate models against observations. Improve understanding of the role of background climate conditions in determining the climate response to the 1991 Pinatubo eruption. The evaluation must take into account the idealized character of VolMIP experiments.", "Forcing: Improve understanding of volcanic radiative forcing and constrain related uncertainties. Volcanic eruptions are among the largest sources of uncertainty in historical radiative forcing .", "Paleo: Evaluate models against paleo reconstructions This objective is motivated by the mismatch between simulated and reconstructed post-eruption surface cooling for volcanic eruptions during the last millennium. The evaluation must take into account the idealized character of VolMIP experiments.", "Predictability: A systematical assessment of regional climate variability - and associated predictability and prediction - during periods of strong volcanic forcing at both intraseasonal-to-seasonal and interannual-to-decadal time scales", "Sensitivity: Improve the characterization of volcanic forcing and associated climate sensitivity through improved understanding of how the hydrological cycle and the large-scale circulation respond to volcanic forcing, through improved understanding of forced responses of the coupled ocean-atmosphere system, and through improved assessment of internal variability.", "Variability: Improve understanding of the mechanism(s) underlying the dynamical climate response to large volcanic eruptions, in particular concerning influence on decadal variability"], "canonicalName": "volmip", "name": "VolMIP", "citations": [{"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "803fa6f5-55a6-4af4-a5ce-c4c2664ed0ff"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "ab7ed4bd-b97f-43be-8a9e-4e053d33e050"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "d537072d-b9c9-48d2-9dfb-65e66b3faeec"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "0d337e18-6df7-46df-be20-d54eb8f5716e"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "87a6c94f-08b4-427c-ac06-e2515c94342d"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "40116ec2-db3e-425a-968c-7445ca5c4ed2"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "3addcf0e-8302-4e86-9ac3-48e40a8fc53d"}, {"meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "type": "cim.2.shared.Citation", "version": 1, "id": "9e139643-3060-4b5b-9869-269f6d66c19b"}], "meta": {"author": {"version": 1, "meta": {"type": "cim.2.shared.DocReference"}, "uid": "253825f3-fbc8-43fb-b1f6-cc575dc693eb"}, "createDate": "2017-03-21 00:00:00", "project": "cmip6-draft", "source": "spreadsheet", "version": 1, "updateDate": "2017-03-21 00:00:00", "type": "cim.2.designing.Project", "id": "b2368e99-26ae-4bf5-915e-504a702b1f4f"}, "rationale": "(a) VolMIP aims at minimizing differences across models in terms of the applied volcanic forcing; (b) Assessing to what extent responses of the coupled ocean\u2013atmosphere system to strong volcanic forcing are robustly simulated across state-of- the-art coupled climate models; (c) identifying the causes that limit robust simulated behaviour, especially differences in their treatment of physical processes.", "longName": "Model Intercomparison Project on the climatic response to Volcanic forcing", "keywords": "volcanic forcing, robust responses, response limitations, decadal variability, attribution", "homepage": "http://volmip.org/cmip6.html", "description": "VolMIP will assess to what extent responses of the coupled ocean-atmosphere system to the same applied strong volcanic forcing are robustly simulated across state-of-the-art coupled climate models and identify the causes that limit robust simulated behavior, especially differences in their treatment of physical processes."}